Their government consists of a President, a Senate, and a Politburo, which seems to occupy the role of a cabinet.

AN: Soon after the end of their migration period, Vlaandia found itself in a crisis when the last king of the Aulfun dynasty was killed in battle against King Pepin I without an heir. Fortunately, a bloody power struggle was averted when Eutharic of the Vlaandian dynasty took his forces to the capital city and seized control before any other nobles could contest him. He soon made enough political bargains and curried enough favor with the the Augustinian church to ensure his hold on the kingdom, before defeating Pepin in a battle at the old capital city. The city was destroyed, however, and Eutharic set up a new capital at Altenstadt, where his great-grandson Theodore rules today.
